post_text:
ONECALL Food Pickup Announcement – 4/15/2020

Good morning, we hope everyone had a safe and enjoyable Easter weekend, under these circumstances.

We want to advise you of an adjustment to our student food pickup program.

Our next food pickup will be this Thursday, April 16th, which includes meals for 5 days. From this point forward, food pickup will be every Thursday, until May 1st or through the end of the school year if the stay at home order remains in place.

One note, the time for pickup at the Chautauqua Center has changed to 10:45 am-11:20 am. All other locations remain the same. Please be prompt as workers must get to other locations.

Thank you and please be safe. Go Indians.

post_text: A wonderful man who was a tireless supporter of public schools and a dear friend. You will be missed greatly. Our thoughts and prayers to his lovely wife Sandy and the entire Diver family, as well as to our community. R.I.P. Ron.
shared_text:
Carlisle, Ohio Lions Club
April 4 at 9:43 PM ·

It’s with deep sadness and a heavy heart that we share a loss of not only our club but the community. Ron Diver, a stand up citizen, a role model to many, a smiling face even when things got tough left us today. There will be a void and we will all miss him. The family will have a private gathering. After the pandemic ceases we will get the opportunity to celebrate the life of a wonderful man. Rest now Lion Ron Diver, until we meet again.

SPRING BREAK STUDENT FOOD PICK-UP ON FRIDAY, APRIL 3

As you are aware, we will be on our scheduled Spring Break next week, which is April 6-10. There will be NO food pick-up during this week.
HOWEVER, this Friday, April 3, we have a food pick-up that will include breakfast and lunch for the 5 days of Spring Break. We will use our current schedule for pick-up and delivery. Additionally, you may want to bring a box, or if walking to a delivery site, bring a wagon, stroller, etc. as we are delivering 5 days worth of food.

Our regular Food Pick-up schedule will resume on Monday, April 13.

Thank you and please be safe.

post_text:
Beginning Monday, March 23rd, we will make an adjustment to our FOOD PICKUP distribution process. Our deliveries will be on Mondays and Wednesdays ONLY, through April 3rd . On Mondays we will deliver lunch and breakfast for 2 days, which will include Monday and Tuesday. On Wednesdays, we will deliver lunch and breakfast for 3 days, which will include Wednesday through Friday. This will allow us more time to restock food supplies. The pickup and delivery locations, as well as times are posted on our district website at www.carlisleindians.org or click on the link below:
https://www.carlisleindians.org/media/districtnews/Food%20Pick%20Up%20-%20REVISED%203-20-2020.pdf

All staff must report to the CHS commons at 8 a.m. Monday, March 16.

post_text:
The Warren County Imagination Library is here! Carlisle Local School District is excited to be a partner in this county-wide effort with the goal that Every Child Reads Every Day!

All Warren County children under five can have a FREE book mailed to THEM every month. Sign up now at www.imaginationlibrary.org

Warren County Imagination Library Founding Partners are Franklin-Springboro Public Library, Lebanon Public Library, Mary L. Cook Public Library, Mason Public Library, Salem Township Public Library, United Way of Warren County, and Warren County Foundation. The five libraries have generously funded a three-year pilot in collaboration with the Ohio Governor’s Imagination Library and Dolly Parton’s Imagination Library.

Please sign up, share this post and join us in The Biggest Civic Engagement in Warren County History – A Generational Change! Questions? Contact the Warren County Imagination Library at 513-934-1001 or info@warrencountyfoundation.org

post_text: Construction on our new school continues at a fast pace. Framing in both the High School and Elementary sections as well as reaching rafter height in both sections. Gym walls are going up fast as well as the the front of the building. Great job by Skanska-Megen our CM.

post_text:
Lots of progress this past week...
1) The 2nd floor of the High School was poured last week. Our next pour will be the Elem. wing July 9.
2) Steel was set in the West part of the Elem. wing. This week steel begins to be set on the East side of Elem. wing.
3) Gym walls have begun and will continue this week.

post_text: It is with great sadness that I tell you about a loss to our school family. Today, Jamie Anderson, a sophomore at Carlisle High School has passed away after apparently being struck by a train sometime in the early morning hours. The incident appears to have been a tragic accident. Please keep Jamie’s family in your thoughts and prayers. Grief counselors were available for our students and staff at the High School today and will continue to be available for the remainder of the week and beyond, if necessary.

GROUNDBREAKING ANNOUNCEMENT:
The Carlisle Local School District Board of Education and the Ohio Facilities Construction Committee are pleased to announce the Groundbreaking Ceremony for the new PK-12 Carlisle Local School building. The ceremony will be held this Tuesday, October 23rd beginning promptly at 12:30 pm. The location will be in the grass area directly behind our current high school. If available, feel free to join us.
